text: The Kaiserstuhl is a small, low Mountain range in Germany. it is located on the Upper Rhine Plain. The ranges rises in the southwest of Baden-Württemberg, Germany. It is in the Emmendingen and Breisgau-Hochschwarzwald ditricts. The mountain range was created by volcanic activiity. ==References== Category:Mountains of Germany Category:Geography of Baden-Württemberg
